## Stop and Flag Rules

Stop and explicitly flag before:
- Adding any new npm package — state what it does and why it's needed
- Modifying `middleware.ts` — state exactly what is changing and why
- Adding Cloudflare cron triggers to `wrangler.toml`
- Writing any `UPDATE` or `DELETE` query against `pods` or `pod_photos`
- Creating any file outside the project structure above

Then wait for confirmation before proceeding.

---

## Performance Guidelines

### Cloudflare Workers Limits
- CPU time: 50ms soft limit — keep queries lean
- Memory: 128MB
- No blocking loops, no N+1 queries

### Query Optimisation
```typescript
// CORRECT — Select only needed columns
const orders = await db.select({
  id: ordersTable.id,
  recipientName: ordersTable.recipientName,
  status: ordersTable.status
}).from(ordersTable);

// WRONG — Never select all on large tables
const orders = await db.select().from(ordersTable);

// CORRECT — Always paginate
const PAGE_SIZE = 50;
const orders = await db.select().from(ordersTable).limit(PAGE_SIZE).offset(page * PAGE_SIZE);
```

