## Git Workflow

```bash
main        # Production
develop     # Development (default working branch)

# Feature branches always cut from develop
git checkout develop
git checkout -b feature/milestone-1-schema
git checkout -b feature/milestone-2-orders
git checkout -b bugfix/driver-offline-sync
```

### Before Every Commit
- [ ] No `console.log` statements left in code
- [ ] No commented-out code
- [ ] `npm run build` passes with zero TypeScript errors
- [ ] Permission checks on every API route
- [ ] Driver queries are scoped to the authenticated driver's ID

### Before Every PR
- [ ] Milestone acceptance criteria met and tested
- [ ] Back office UI tested on desktop
- [ ] Driver UI tested on mobile (375px) and iPad (768px)
- [ ] No security issues introduced
- [ ] `npm run build` clean

---

## Milestone Testing Checklist

Before marking any milestone complete:
- [ ] Feature works end-to-end — not just UI, but data saving and reading correctly
- [ ] Back office role cannot access driver routes and vice versa
- [ ] All API routes have permission checks
- [ ] `npm run build` passes with no TypeScript errors
- [ ] No console errors in browser
- [ ] Responsive on the correct breakpoints for the interface (back office = desktop, driver = mobile)
- [ ] All tap targets in driver app are minimum 48×48px
- [ ] Inputs in driver app have `font-size: 16px` minimum
- [ ] Acceptance criteria from the spec met

---

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

**Never:**
- Use Node.js-only APIs (`fs`, `path`, `buffer`, etc.) — this runs on Cloudflare Workers
- Use `drizzle-kit push` — always generate and migrate
- Connect to Neon directly — always go through Hyperdrive
- Expose raw R2 URLs — always use signed URLs
- Allow a driver to query another driver's data
- Modify or delete a POD record
- Commit `.env.local` or any secrets
- Use `console.log` for sensitive data (GPS, signatures, personal details)
- Skip HMAC verification on Shopify webhooks
- Use `text-sm` on inputs in the driver app (causes iOS zoom)

**Always:**
- Check `docs/alaseel-pod-spec.md` before implementing
- Scope driver queries to the authenticated driver
- Validate Shopify webhook HMAC before processing
- Generate signed R2 URLs at read time
- Handle the offline case in the driver app
- Test driver UI on mobile viewport before calling a milestone done
- Run `npm run build` before committing
